Georgia had a mixed at-large/district system for the 1st Congress. Representatives were elected at-large, but for three district-based seats.

District Result Candidates
Georgia 1
"Lower district" 		Anti-Administration win √ James Jackson (Anti-Administration) 50.9%
William Houstoun 33.6%
Henry Osborne 14.5%
James Seagrove 0.6%
Others 0.4%

"Middle district" 		Anti-Administration win √ Abraham Baldwin (Anti-Administration) 69.0%
Henry Osborne 15.2%
Joseph Sumner 10.4%
Isaac Briggs 2.7%
William Houstoun 1.5%

Georgia 3
"Upper district" 		Anti-Administration win √ George Mathews (Anti-Administration) 96.5%
